# Project Structure & Architecture

This is a Deno-based CMS scripts project for managing Strapi and Prismic content. The project follows a modular architecture with clear separation of concerns.

## Core Architecture

### Entry Points

- [run.ts](mdc:run.ts) - Main entry point that routes to different modules
- [strapi/main.ts](mdc:strapi/main.ts) - Strapi module entry point with function registry
- [prismic/main.ts](mdc:prismic/main.ts) - Prismic module entry point

### Module Structure

Each module (strapi, prismic) follows this pattern:

- `main.ts` - Function registry and CLI interface
- `services/` - Business logic services
- `config/` - Configuration and constants
- `utils/` - Utility functions
- `data/` - Data files (CSV, JSON, PDFs, thumbnails)

### Service Layer Pattern

Services extend base classes and follow dependency injection:

- [StrapiService](mdc:strapi/services/strapi/strapi.service.ts) - Base service for Strapi operations
- [FormService](mdc:strapi/services/form/form.service.ts) - Form management operations
- [CategoryService](mdc:strapi/services/category/category.service.ts) - Category operations
- [UploadService](mdc:strapi/services/upload/upload.service.ts) - File upload operations

### Configuration Management

- [settings.ts](mdc:strapi/config/settings.ts) - Main configuration with LT_CARD constant
- [enum.ts](mdc:strapi/config/enum.ts) - Type definitions and enums
- Environment variables loaded via `@std/dotenv`

### Data Organization

- `data/csv/` - CSV import files with LT-* naming convention
- `data/json/` - JSON exports and configuration
- `data/pdf/` - PDF files organized by LT card
- `data/thumbnails/` - Generated thumbnail images
- `data/mapping-template/` - ID mapping files
- `logs/` - Error logs and processing reports

## Import Path Conventions

- Use `@strapi/` prefix for strapi module imports
- Use `@prismic/` prefix for prismic module imports
- Use `@std/` for Deno standard library imports
- Use `@shared/` for shared utilities (if any)

## Function Registry Pattern

Functions are registered in `main.ts` with configuration:

```typescript
export const functions = {
  functionName: () => service.method(),
};

export const functionConfigs = {
  functionName: { heavy?: boolean; media?: boolean }
};
```

## Environment Handling

- Use `isProductionEnv()` helper to determine environment
- Environment-specific file paths in constants
- Production vs staging data separation
